LONDON , May 4 -LRB- Xinhua -RRB- -- <ENAMEX TYPE="VITAL">A case of BSE , known as mad cow disease , has been confirmed in the Irish Republic for the first time since the wave of the current British -based scare over the disease was stirred up in March , reported BBC TV today .</ENAMEX>
The discovery , in a cow in County Cork last month , led to the slaughter of 183 animals on the farm involved .
Under the policy of the Irish government , the BSE -infected cattle will be automatically slaughtered so as to prevent the disease from being spread .
